---
import PageLayout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '~/components/directory/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import config from '~/config';

const title = 'Privacy Policy';
const description = `Privacy policy for ${config.brandName}. Learn how ${config.brandName} collects, uses, shares, and protects your personal information.`;
const metadata = { title, description };
const currentYear = new Date().getFullYear();
const effectiveDate = 'March 17, 2026';
---
<PageLayout metadata={metadata}>
  <Fragment slot="announcement"><span></span></Fragment>
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-8">
    <Breadcrumbs crumbs={[{ label: 'Privacy Policy' }]} />

    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-default mb-6">Privacy Policy</h1>

    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <p class="text-sm text-muted">Effective Date: {effectiveDate} &mdash; Last Updated: {effectiveDate}</p>

      <p>
        {config.brandName} ("we," "us," or "our") operates the website <a href={config.siteUrl}>{config.domain}</a> (the "Site").
        This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you visit the Site,
        submit a quote request, claim a business listing, or otherwise interact with our services. Please read this policy
        carefully. By using the Site, you consent to the practices described in this Privacy Policy.
      </p>

      <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>

      <h3>a. Information from Attorneys and Site Visitors</h3>
      <p>When you use our "Request a Quote" forms, we collect the following information you voluntarily provide:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Full name</li>
        <li>Email address</li>
        <li>Phone number</li>
        <li>Case details and project description</li>
        <li>Preferred dates and location</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We do not require you to create an account to browse the directory or submit quote requests.
      </p>

      <h3>b. Information from Service Providers (Listed Businesses)</h3>
      <p>When {config.primaryKeyword}s claim or manage their listings, we may collect:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Business name, address, phone number, and website</li>
        <li>Contact name and email address (used for magic link authentication)</li>
        <li>Business description, service areas, and specializations</li>
        <li>Uploaded photos and media</li>
        <li>Certifications, credentials, and professional affiliations</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>c. Business Listing Data from Public Sources</h3>
      <p>
        {config.brandName} compiles business listing information from publicly available sources, including but not limited to:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Google Maps and Google Business Profiles</li>
        <li>Professional registries, licensing boards, and trade associations</li>
        <li>Publicly available business directories and review platforms</li>
        <li>Public-facing business websites</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        This publicly sourced data may include business names, addresses, phone numbers, websites, service descriptions,
        review ratings, and other information that businesses have made publicly available. We aggregate and organize this
        information to help attorneys find qualified {config.primaryKeyword}s.
      </p>

      <h3>d. Automatically Collected Information</h3>
      <p>When you visit the Site, certain information may be collected automatically:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Log data</strong> — IP address, browser type, operating system, referring URL, pages visited, and timestamps (collected by our hosting provider, Cloudflare)</li>
        <li><strong>Session cookies</strong> — Used for provider dashboard authentication (see Section 4)</li>
        <li><strong>Analytics data</strong> — If enabled, Google Analytics (GA4) may collect anonymized usage data such as page views, session duration, and general geographic location</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <p>We use the information we collect for the following purposes:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Facilitating connections</strong> — Forwarding your quote request details to the {config.primaryKeyword}(s) you select so they can respond to your inquiry</li>
        <li><strong>Operating the directory</strong> — Maintaining accurate, up-to-date business listings for {config.primaryKeyword}s across the United States</li>
        <li><strong>Provider authentication</strong> — Sending magic link emails to verify provider identity when claiming or managing listings</li>
        <li><strong>Transactional communications</strong> — Sending quote request confirmations, claim verification emails, and listing update notifications</li>
        <li><strong>Improving the Site</strong> — Analyzing aggregated usage patterns to improve content, navigation, and user experience</li>
        <li><strong>Legal compliance</strong> — Responding to legal requests, enforcing our terms, and protecting our rights</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We do not use your personal information for advertising, profiling, or automated decision-making.</p>

      <h2>3. How We Share Your Information</h2>
      <p>We do not sell your personal information. We share information only in the following limited circumstances:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Quote requests</strong> — When you submit a quote request, your name, email, phone number, and case details
          are forwarded to the selected {config.primaryKeyword}(s) so they can respond to your inquiry. Once shared, that
          provider's use of your information is governed by their own privacy practices.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Service providers</strong> — We use third-party services to operate the Site (see Section 9). These providers
          process data on our behalf and are contractually obligated to protect your information.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Legal requirements</strong> — We may disclose information if required by law, subpoena, court order, or
          governmental regulation, or if we believe disclosure is necessary to protect our rights, your safety, or the safety of others.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Business transfers</strong> — In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of all or a portion of our assets,
          personal information may be transferred as part of that transaction. We will notify affected users of any change in
          ownership or control of their personal information.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
      <p>The Site uses a minimal number of cookies:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Session cookies (essential)</strong> — When {config.primaryKeyword}s log in to manage their listings via
          magic link authentication, we set a session cookie to maintain their authenticated state. These cookies expire when
          the browser session ends or after a set period of inactivity.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Cloudflare cookies (essential)</strong> — Our hosting provider, Cloudflare, may set cookies for security
          purposes (e.g., bot detection and DDoS protection). These are strictly necessary for the Site to function.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Analytics cookies (optional)</strong> — If Google Analytics (GA4) is enabled, it may set cookies to collect
          anonymized usage data. Google Analytics data is used solely to understand aggregate usage patterns and improve the Site.
          You can opt out of Google Analytics by installing the
          <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on</a>.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We do not use advertising cookies, retargeting pixels, or social media tracking scripts. Our client-side search
        (powered by Pagefind) operates entirely in your browser and does not transmit search queries to any server.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Data Retention</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Quote requests</strong> — Quote request data is forwarded to the selected provider(s) and retained in our
          systems for up to 12 months to handle disputes or follow-up inquiries, after which it is deleted.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Provider accounts</strong> — Provider listing data is retained for as long as the listing is active. Providers
          may request deletion of their account and associated data at any time (see Section 7).
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Business listing data</strong> — Publicly sourced business information is retained and periodically updated
          for as long as the business appears to be active. Businesses may request removal at any time (see Section 7).
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Server logs</strong> — Cloudflare server logs are retained according to
          <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Cloudflare's data retention policies</a>.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Analytics data</strong> — If Google Analytics is enabled, data is retained for up to 14 months per Google's default settings.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>6. Your Privacy Rights</h2>

      <h3>a. All Users</h3>
      <p>Regardless of where you reside, you may:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Request access to the personal information we hold about you</li>
        <li>Request correction of inaccurate personal information</li>
        <li>Request deletion of your personal information</li>
        <li>Withdraw consent for future communications</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To exercise any of these rights, contact us at
        <a href={`mailto:${config.contactEmail}`}>{config.contactEmail}</a>. We will respond to verified requests within 30 days.
      </p>

      <h3>b. California Residents (CCPA/CPRA)</h3>
      <p>
        If you are a California resident, the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) and the California Privacy Rights Act (CPRA)
        provide you with additional rights regarding your personal information:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Right to Know</strong> — You have the right to request that we disclose the categories and specific pieces of
          personal information we have collected about you, the categories of sources from which it was collected, the business
          purpose for collecting it, and the categories of third parties with whom we share it.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Right to Delete</strong> — You have the right to request the deletion of personal information we have collected
          from you, subject to certain exceptions permitted by law.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Right to Correct</strong> — You have the right to request correction of inaccurate personal information we
          maintain about you.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Right to Opt-Out of Sale or Sharing</strong> — <strong>We do not sell or share your personal information</strong>
          for cross-context behavioral advertising. Because we do not engage in these activities, there is no need to opt out.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Right to Non-Discrimination</strong> — We will not discriminate against you for exercising any of your CCPA/CPRA rights.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To submit a CCPA request, email <a href={`mailto:${config.contactEmail}`}>{config.contactEmail}</a> with the subject line
        "CCPA Request." We will verify your identity before processing your request and respond within 45 days as required by law.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Business Listing Data: Corrections and Removal</h2>
      <p>
        {config.brandName} aggregates business information from publicly available sources to help attorneys find qualified
        {config.primaryKeyword}s. We strive to keep all listings accurate and current.
      </p>
      <p>If you are a business owner or authorized representative, you may:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Claim your listing</strong> — Verify your identity and take control of your listing to update business details, add photos, and manage your profile</li>
        <li><strong>Request corrections</strong> — Ask us to correct any inaccurate information displayed on your listing</li>
        <li><strong>Request removal</strong> — Ask us to remove your business listing from the directory entirely</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To request a correction or removal, email <a href={`mailto:${config.contactEmail}`}>{config.contactEmail}</a> with
        your business name, the URL of the listing in question, and the nature of your request. We will process correction
        and removal requests within 5 business days.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        The Site is not directed at children under the age of 13, and we do not knowingly collect personal information from
        children under 13. If we learn that we have inadvertently collected personal information from a child under 13, we
        will take steps to delete that information as quickly as possible. If you believe a child under 13 has provided us
        with personal information, please contact us at <a href={`mailto:${config.contactEmail}`}>{config.contactEmail}</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>We use the following third-party services to operate the Site. Each has its own privacy policy governing data it processes:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Cloudflare</strong> — Website hosting, content delivery network (CDN), DNS, and security services.
          <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Cloudflare Privacy Policy</a>.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Amazon Simple Email Service (SES)</strong> — Transactional email delivery for quote request notifications,
          magic link authentication, and listing claim communications.
          <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/privacy/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">AWS Privacy Notice</a>.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>OpenStreetMap / Leaflet</strong> — Interactive maps displaying provider locations. Map tiles are loaded from
          OpenStreetMap tile servers, which may log your IP address.
          <a href="https://wiki.osmfoundation.org/wiki/Privacy_Policy" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">OpenStreetMap Privacy Policy</a>.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Google Analytics (GA4)</strong> — If enabled, anonymized website usage analytics.
          <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Google Privacy Policy</a>.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We do not use any advertising networks, social media plugins, or third-party tracking services beyond those listed above.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Data Security</h2>
      <p>
        We implement reasonable administrative, technical, and physical safeguards to protect your personal information,
        including encrypted connections (HTTPS/TLS) for all data transmitted to and from the Site, secure email-based
        authentication for provider accounts, and access controls limiting who can view personal data within our systems.
      </p>
      <p>
        However, no method of transmission over the internet or method of electronic storage is 100% secure. While we strive
        to protect your personal information, we cannot guarantee its absolute security.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices, technologies, legal
        requirements, or other factors. When we make material changes, we will update the "Last Updated" date at the top
        of this page. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically.
      </p>
      <p>
        If we make changes that materially affect how we handle personal information you have previously provided, we will
        make reasonable efforts to notify you (such as by posting a prominent notice on the Site).
      </p>

      <h2>12. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>If you have questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or our data practices, you may contact us at:</p>
      <address class="not-italic">
        <strong>{config.brandName}</strong><br />
        PO Box 1547<br />
        Austin, TX 78767<br /><br />
        Email: <a href={`mailto:${config.contactEmail}`}>{config.contactEmail}</a><br />
        Website: <a href={config.siteUrl}>{config.domain}</a>
      </address>

      <p class="text-sm text-muted mt-8">
        &copy; {currentYear} {config.brandName}. All rights reserved.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</PageLayout>
